cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper focuses on dense pixelwise prediction, which is a common task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new module that can be easily combined with existing FCNs, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as neural networks. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the computational cost and model size, which are related to optimization and efficiency, respectively. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents results on human pose estimation, semantic segmentation, and object detection, which are all sub-tasks of CV. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category.
